rman origin): nickname for a man of swarthy complexion, from Middle High German <i>mōr</i>, German <i>Mohr</i>, and Middle Dutch <i>moor</i> ‘Moor’.","German: from a short form of an old personal name, <i>Morhart</i> (see   Morath  )."]}]},{"name":"Cormac","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional Irish name, of uncertain origin. It has been a very popular name in Ireland from the earliest times, and in modern times has been taken up in the wider English-speaking world ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Cormac MacCarthy Mor King of Desmond was born in 1271, in Diocese of Kerry, Ireland, his father, Donal Oge MacCarthy Mor, was 32 and his mother, Julia Lynch, was 27. He married Honoria FitzMaurice in 1303, in Diocese of Kerry, Ireland. They were the parents of at least 7 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1359, in his hometown, at the age of 88."},"et":{"1271–1359":"1271–1359","1255–Female":"1255–Surnud","1280–1305":"1280–1305","1303–1390":"1303–1390","1310–1368":"1310–1368","1312–Male":"1312–Surnud","1314–Male":"1314–Surnud","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1316–Male":"1316–Surnud","1318–Male":"1318–Surnud","1324–Male":"1324–Surnud","1239–1307":"1239–1307","1244–Female":"1244–Surnud","1271":"1271","1390":"1390","1280":"1280","1305":"1305","1316":"1316","1239":"1239","1315":"1315","1359":"1359","1303":"1303","1314":"1314","1324":"1324","1368":"1368","1312":"1312","1310":"1310","1244":"1244","1255":"1255","1307":"1307","1318":"1318","Desmond, Kerry, Munster, Ireland":"Diocese of Kerry, Iirimaa","Desmond, Kerry, Ireland":"County Kerry, Iirimaa","Cork, Ireland":"County Cork, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1271–1359":"1271–1359","1255–Female":"1255–Kuollut","1280–1305":"1280–1305","1303–1390":"1303–1390","1310–1368":"1310–1368","1312–Male":"1312–Kuollut","1314–Male":"1314–Kuollut","1315–Female":"1315–Kuollut","1316–Male":"1316–Kuollut","1318–Male":"1318–Kuollut","1324–Male":"1324–Kuollut","1239–1